cs.DS, cs.DC, cs.CE, cs.DM, cs.LG 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category as the paper presents a new algorithm for constructing the BWT and FM-index of large string sets, which is a fundamental data structure in bioinformatics and text processing. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the algorithm is designed for massive parallelism and can exploit GPU accelerated systems. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is a possible category as the algorithm is relevant for processing large genomic data sets produced by Next Generation Sequencing, which is a common application in computational biology and bioinformatics. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is another possible category as the paper involves the analysis of memory usage and time complexity of the algorithm. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a less likely category as the paper does not involve any machine learning techniques, but the algorithm may be useful for processing large datasets in machine learning applications.
